  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Prepare a breading station with panko breadcrumbs, egg, and double-fry inspired seasoning blend.",
    "Season the fish fillets with coriander seeds, sugar, and salt.",
    "Dredge the fish fillets in the breading station, pressing the crumbs onto the fish to adhere.",
    "Heat coconut oil in a large non-stick skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Cook the breaded fish fillets for 3-4 minutes per side, until golden brown and crispy.",
    "Transfer the fish to a baking sheet and drizzle with mirin and fish sauce.",
    "Bake in the preheated oven for 8-10 minutes, until cooked through.",
    "Garnish with fresh cilantro, if desired.",
    "Serve immediately."
